message.reasoning_content:
I need to respond to all 10 statements about AI in education as a primary or secondary school teacher from Republic of North Macedonia. Let me go through each statement and provide thoughtful responses based on my perspective as an educator.

[TT4G35A] - Artificial intelligence helps teachers write or improve lesson plans.
This is a positive use of AI. AI can indeed help generate ideas, improve structure, and provide suggestions for lesson plans. I would say I "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35B] - Artificial intelligence enables teachers to adapt learning material to different students' abilities.
AI can analyze student performance and suggest adaptations. This is a legitimate benefit. I would "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35C] - Artificial intelligence assists teachers in supporting students individually.
AI can help provide personalized feedback and support. I would "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35D] - Artificial intelligence supports students with specific needs (e.g. multilingual learners, students with special education needs).
AI tools can provide language support and customized learning experiences. I would "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35E] - Artificial intelligence helps teachers automate administrative tasks.
AI can definitely help with grading, attendance, scheduling etc. I would "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35F] - Artificial intelligence enables students to misrepresent others' work as their own.
This is a concern - students can use AI to generate work and present it as their own. I would "Agree" with this as a concern/risk.

[TT4G35G] - Artificial intelligence makes recommendations that may not be appropriate or correct.
This is a valid concern - AI can make errors or provide misleading information. I would "Agree" with this as a risk.

[TT4G35H] - Artificial intelligence amplifies biases that reinforce students' misconceptions.
This is a known issue with AI - it can perpetuate biases in training data. I would "Agree" with this as a concern.
 
[TT4G35I] - Artificial intelligence jeopardises the privacy and security of student data.
Data protection is a significant concern when implementing AI systems in schools. I would "Agree" with this as a risk.

[TT4G35J] - Artificial intelligence suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches that teachers would use with students.
AI might recommend teaching methods that lack pedagogical soundness or aren't appropriate for my students' context. I would "Agree" with this as a concern.
